tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, suggesting possible renal impairment and abnormal glucose metabolism, despite low HbA1c. Urine is cloudy, brown, with low specific gravity, but no evidence of infection (negative nitrite/leukocytes). Further evaluation for acute or chronic kidney disease and possible non-diabetic causes of glucosuria/ketonuria is recommended. Clinical correlation advised.
